Lagos State Governor, Mr. Babajide Sanwo-Olu on Thursday said five more Coronavirus patients have been discharged from isolation centre in the state. According to the governor, those discharged included three female and two male. Sanwo-Olu said, “Dear Lagosians, Today, five more patients; three females and two males, have been discharged from the Mainland Infectious Diseases Hospital to reunite with the society. “They were discharged having recovered fully and tested negative twice consecutively to #COVID19”. Sanwo-Olu said the figure brought to 90, the number of patients successfully managed and discharged from the state’s isolation facilities. “I appeal to residents to stay at home, practice Social Distancing and observe the highest possible personal and hand hygiene,” he said. 